In [179]:
def plot_decompose(decompose):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(4, 1, sharey=False, sharex=True)
    plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.1)
    fig.set_figwidth(14)
    fig.set_figheight(22)
    
    axes[0].plot(decompose.observed.index, decompose.observed, label='Observed')
    axes[0].set_xticks(decompose.trend.index[::7])
    axes[0].tick_params(labelrotation=45)
    axes[0].set_title('Observed')
    
    axes[1].plot(decompose.trend.index, decompose.trend, label='Trend')
    axes[1].set_xticks(decompose.trend.index[::7])
    axes[1].tick_params(labelrotation=45)
    axes[1].set_title('Trend')
    
    axes[2].plot(decompose.seasonal.index, decompose.seasonal, label='Seasonal')
    axes[2].set_xticks(decompose.seasonal.index[::7])
    axes[2].tick_params(labelrotation=45)
    axes[2].set_title('Seasonal')
    
    axes[3].plot(decompose.resid.index, decompose.resid, label='Resid')
    axes[3].set_xticks(decompose.resid.index[::7])
    axes[3].tick_params(labelrotation=45)
    axes[3].set_title('Resid')
    
    plt.show()

def plot_week_season(decompose, first_day=2):
    WEEK = ['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 
            'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday']
    plt.plot(WEEK, decompose.seasonal[7-first_day:7-first_day+7])
    plt.title('Seasonal for week')
    plt.show()

In [214]:
def adftest(ts):
    dftest = adfuller(ts, maxlag=7, autolag=None)
    dfoutput = pd.Series(dftest[0:4], index=['Test Statistic','p-value','#Lags Used','Number of Observations Used'])
    print(dfoutput)
    print()
    if dfoutput['p-value'] <= 0.05:
        print('>>> Stationary')
    else:
        print('>>> Non-stationary')

def autocorr(ts):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 7))
    sm.graphics.tsa.plot_acf(ts, lags=15, ax=ax, adjusted=True, alpha=0.05)
    plt.show()
